      <hedline>
        <hl1>When Knowledge Runs Into Stage Fright</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bogdan Fryszczyn letter on May 31 cites success of home-schooled children in National Geography Bee; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Girls a Distant 2nd in Geography Gap Among U.S. Pupils'' (front page, May 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Girls a Distant 2nd in Geography Gap Among U.S. Pupils'' (front page, May 31):</p>
        <p>You note that 4 of the 10 finalists in this year's National Geography Bee were schooled at home. In light of the objections of teachers' unions to home schooling, they owe us an explanation of what went wrong with the education of those four finalists.</p>
        <p>BOGDAN FRYSZCZYN  South Plainfield, N.J., June 1, 2000</p>
      </block>
